description:
&lt;p&gt;Exemplar is on the lookout for a new Team Manager/System Coordinator to support the expanding project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CPFT were chosen as one of the national exemplar pilot sites for the redesign and transformation of primary and community mental health care to develop and deliver a new service paradigm in line with the NHSE community mental health transformation agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The goal of this transformation project is to develop and deliver a new service model that seeks to provide a more seamless pathway of mental health care and eliminate current gaps between services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting opportunity has emerged, and we are looking to recruit a leadership role that will work alongside the clinical programme manager and wider project team and new stepped care model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post would be suitable for candidates with existing management experience but who is comfortable with a fast pace of working with developing structures and processes. The post holder will be initially working with the transformation team in Peterborough and the role is expected to develop, as the transformation project works its way across the county, and eventually the post holder will be managing one of the Exemplar pathways as they are configured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam Swinden - Clinical Programme Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam.Swinden@cpft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07866 940749&lt;/p&gt;
